{
  "id": "2021-09-30_screen_english",
  "date": "2021-09-30",
  "corner": "screen_english",
  "corner_label": "Screen English",
  "title": "",
  "movie": "코다 (CODA)",
  "duration_sec": 681.17,
  "audio_url": "https://rtyzdyyfahddqshgyjvn.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/gmp-audio/2021-09-30_screen_english.mp3",
  "artwork_generated_url": "",
  "script": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 0.92,
      "text": "Hello! Good morning!"
    },
    {
      "start": 1.08,
      "end": 2.72,
      "text": "임선화 님께서"
    },
    {
      "start": 2.72,
      "end": 6.84,
      "text": "조크쌤 케미는 항상 아침에 즐거운 기운을 선사해요."
    },
    {
      "start": 6.96,
      "end": 8.5,
      "text": "웃음 웃음 감사합니다. 웃음 웃음"
    },
    {
      "start": 8.5,
      "end": 10.92,
      "text": "오늘도 족쌤과 함께"
    },
    {
      "start": 10.92,
      "end": 12.08,
      "text": "Let's go!"
    },
    {
      "start": 12.14,
      "end": 14.88,
      "text": "오늘도 한번 케미 뿜뿜 해보도록 하겠습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 15.02,
      "end": 15.5,
      "text": "뿜뿜뿜뿜"
    },
    {
      "start": 15.5,
      "end": 19.64,
      "text": "Anyway, I can tell it's one of the best movies of the year."
    },
    {
      "start": 19.84,
      "end": 21.68,
      "text": "Honestly, I loved it."
    },
    {
      "start": 21.88,
      "end": 22.88,
      "text": "I'm honest."
    },
    {
      "start": 23.1,
      "end": 24.54,
      "text": "I'm being completely honest."
    },
    {
      "start": 24.62,
      "end": 28.34,
      "text": "진짜 진심을 가득 담아가지고 표현을 해주고 계시네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 28.5,
      "end": 31.14,
      "text": "이 CODA의 영화에 감동을 참 많이 받았는데"
    },
    {
      "start": 31.14,
      "end": 35.04,
      "text": "이 영화는 features a number of classic songs"
    },
    {
      "start": 35.04,
      "end": 40.54,
      "text": "including pieces by Joni Mitchell, Marvin Gaye, and David Bowie."
    },
    {
      "start": 40.68,
      "end": 44.46,
      "text": "Yeah, many songs that many Koreans will be familiar with."
    },
    {
      "start": 44.64,
      "end": 46.02,
      "text": "Classic pop songs."
    },
    {
      "start": 46.84,
      "end": 49.06,
      "text": "Also, my wife, when she heard"
    },
    {
      "start": 49.06,
      "end": 51.54,
      "text": "you know the last song in the movie?"
    },
    {
      "start": 51.66,
      "end": 52.78,
      "text": "The Audition."
    },
    {
      "start": 52.98,
      "end": 55.56,
      "text": "Yeah, Both Sides Now is the title of the song."
    },
    {
      "start": 55.56,
      "end": 57.52,
      "text": "Both Sides Now by Joni Mitchell."
    },
    {
      "start": 57.74,
      "end": 58.98,
      "text": "That was beautiful."
    },
    {
      "start": 58.98,
      "end": 61.58,
      "text": "It was actually my first time to hear that song."
    },
    {
      "start": 62.08,
      "end": 62.84,
      "text": "But my wife said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 62.92,
      "end": 64.24,
      "text": "어디서 들었지?"
    },
    {
      "start": 64.6,
      "end": 68.48,
      "text": "She remembered, she heard that song from a commercial,"
    },
    {
      "start": 68.8,
      "end": 70.42,
      "text": "an old commercial in Korea"
    },
    {
      "start": 70.42,
      "end": 72.52,
      "text": "for a clothing brand"
    },
    {
      "start": 72.52,
      "end": 74.24,
      "text": "with Daniel Henney"
    },
    {
      "start": 74.24,
      "end": 76.9,
      "text": "and Paltrow,"
    },
    {
      "start": 77.3,
      "end": 78.04,
      "text": "Gwyneth Paltrow,"
    },
    {
      "start": 78.22,
      "end": 79.5,
      "text": "the famous actress."
    },
    {
      "start": 79.7,
      "end": 80.84,
      "text": "They did a commercial,"
    },
    {
      "start": 81.2,
      "end": 83.62,
      "text": "a clothing commercial for a famous Korean brand."
    },
    {
      "start": 83.62,
      "end": 87.82,
      "text": "Daniel Henney가 나와서 더 인상 깊게 음악을 들으신 게 아닐까?"
    },
    {
      "start": 88.98,
      "end": 89.5,
      "text": "No."
    },
    {
      "start": 90.3,
      "end": 91.74,
      "text": "Well, 이제 안 좋아요, 이제."
    },
    {
      "start": 92.54,
      "end": 93.08,
      "text": "아무튼."
    },
    {
      "start": 93.2,
      "end": 94.4,
      "text": "아무튼 거기서 나갔대요."
    },
    {
      "start": 94.44,
      "end": 94.68,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 95.22,
      "end": 96.12,
      "text": "그러면 크리스 씨네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 96.2,
      "end": 98.78,
      "text": "What's the most memorable song out of the OST?"
    },
    {
      "start": 99.12,
      "end": 100.36,
      "text": "It was that song"
    },
    {
      "start": 100.36,
      "end": 101.62,
      "text": "until you mentioned"
    },
    {
      "start": 101.62,
      "end": 102.92,
      "text": "Daniel Henney."
    },
    {
      "start": 103.08,
      "end": 104.66,
      "text": "저도 마찬가지로."
    },
    {
      "start": 104.8,
      "end": 105.42,
      "text": "I like that."
    },
    {
      "start": 105.48,
      "end": 105.68,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 106.28,
      "end": 107.38,
      "text": "이 Both Sides Now"
    },
    {
      "start": 107.38,
      "end": 110.08,
      "text": "라는 곡을 가장 인상 깊게 들었어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 110.3,
      "end": 111.04,
      "text": "It was touching."
    },
    {
      "start": 111.04,
      "end": 111.48,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 111.9,
      "end": 114.6,
      "text": "특히 그 마지막 오디션 장면에서"
    },
    {
      "start": 114.6,
      "end": 117.76,
      "text": "이 곡을 불렀었던 장면이 있었습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 117.9,
      "end": 118.62,
      "text": "And her family,"
    },
    {
      "start": 118.72,
      "end": 121.64,
      "text": "my favorite part was when her family came in the audition room."
    },
    {
      "start": 121.7,
      "end": 122.16,
      "text": "Right."
    },
    {
      "start": 122.48,
      "end": 123.48,
      "text": "They were on the balcony."
    },
    {
      "start": 123.72,
      "end": 124.22,
      "text": "Yeah, yeah, yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 124.3,
      "end": 125.3,
      "text": "And they were watching her."
    },
    {
      "start": 125.3,
      "end": 127.88,
      "text": "So she started sign language,"
    },
    {
      "start": 128.08,
      "end": 129.66,
      "text": "doing sign language while singing."
    },
    {
      "start": 129.9,
      "end": 131.28,
      "text": "And the judges were like,"
    },
    {
      "start": 131.34,
      "end": 132.28,
      "text": "Who's here?"
    },
    {
      "start": 132.46,
      "end": 133.12,
      "text": "What's happening?"
    },
    {
      "start": 133.38,
      "end": 134.5,
      "text": "But she didn't care."
    },
    {
      "start": 134.58,
      "end": 135.18,
      "text": "눈치 안 보고."
    },
    {
      "start": 135.36,
      "end": 135.64,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 135.74,
      "end": 136.92,
      "text": "She was trying to,"
    },
    {
      "start": 137.02,
      "end": 137.8,
      "text": "that was her love."
    },
    {
      "start": 137.94,
      "end": 139.54,
      "text": "She was showing love for her parents."
    },
    {
      "start": 139.62,
      "end": 139.86,
      "text": "Right."
    },
    {
      "start": 139.96,
      "end": 141.66,
      "text": "For bringing her all the way to this audition."
    },
    {
      "start": 141.8,
      "end": 144.58,
      "text": "Oh, 그래서 I couldn't help crying in that scene."
    },
    {
      "start": 144.92,
      "end": 146.18,
      "text": "I shed some tears too."
    },
    {
      "start": 146.28,
      "end": 148.06,
      "text": "저도 엄청 울었어요, 그 장면에서."
    },
    {
      "start": 148.16,
      "end": 148.44,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 148.44,
      "end": 150.14,
      "text": "가슴을 막 부여잡고 울었어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 150.8,
      "end": 151.88,
      "text": "It really got to me."
    },
    {
      "start": 152.1,
      "end": 153.02,
      "text": "It hit you too."
    },
    {
      "start": 153.18,
      "end": 153.48,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 153.84,
      "end": 157.5,
      "text": "모두가 하나가 되는 그런 장면이 아니지 않나 싶습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 157.68,
      "end": 158.0,
      "text": "Beautiful."
    },
    {
      "start": 158.46,
      "end": 160.28,
      "text": "네, 먼저 이 장면 듣고 오겠습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 160.28,
      "end": 161.52,
      "text": "All right."
    },
    {
      "start": 161.86,
      "end": 163.86,
      "text": "You are just going to have to sing an acapella."
    },
    {
      "start": 166.46,
      "end": 167.56,
      "text": "I can accompany her."
    },
    {
      "start": 168.08,
      "end": 169.04,
      "text": "Sorry for interrupting."
    },
    {
      "start": 169.84,
      "end": 170.02,
      "text": "Hi."
    },
    {
      "start": 170.95,
      "end": 171.67,
      "text": "How are you?"
    },
    {
      "start": 172.47,
      "end": 174.27,
      "text": "I'm Bernardo Villalobos."
    },
    {
      "start": 175.01,
      "end": 175.69,
      "text": "Class of 89."
    },
    {
      "start": 176.71,
      "end": 177.55,
      "text": "Nice to see you all."
    },
    {
      "start": 178.4,
      "end": 179.02,
      "text": "May I?"
    },
    {
      "start": 179.78,
      "end": 180.48,
      "text": "I guess so."
    },
    {
      "start": 180.62,
      "end": 181.44,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "start": 181.86,
      "end": 183.72,
      "text": "What's going on?"
    },
    {
      "start": 189.55,
      "end": 198.09,
      "text": "That's the song."
    },
    {
      "start": 198.21,
      "end": 202.67,
      "text": "Yeah, dramatically her family sent her to the audition."
    },
    {
      "start": 203.29,
      "end": 203.93,
      "text": "They did."
    },
    {
      "start": 204.03,
      "end": 204.33,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 204.49,
      "end": 206.55,
      "text": "I didn't think they were going to."
    },
    {
      "start": 206.55,
      "end": 208.73,
      "text": "저도 전혀 예상하지 못했어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 209.13,
      "end": 213.05,
      "text": "가족들이 막판에 오디션에 보내게 됩니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 213.19,
      "end": 214.13,
      "text": "At the last minute."
    },
    {
      "start": 214.29,
      "end": 214.49,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 214.61,
      "end": 216.39,
      "text": "Okay, we're taking you to the audition."
    },
    {
      "start": 216.73,
      "end": 219.55,
      "text": "그리고 그 과정에서 her brother 있잖아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 219.55,
      "end": 222.05,
      "text": "wholeheartedly supported her."
    },
    {
      "start": 222.73,
      "end": 227.07,
      "text": "Ruby의 오빠가 바닷가에서 내가 너를 응원해."
    },
    {
      "start": 227.29,
      "end": 228.53,
      "text": "너 정말 재능이 있잖아."
    },
    {
      "start": 228.75,
      "end": 233.53,
      "text": "라고 하면서 격려해 주고 하는 부분이 참 nice scene이었다고 생각합니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 233.53,
      "end": 239.33,
      "text": "Yeah, at first she was angry that she was going to give up her dream and stay with the family."
    },
    {
      "start": 239.47,
      "end": 240.59,
      "text": "We don't need you."
    },
    {
      "start": 240.83,
      "end": 241.43,
      "text": "Just go."
    },
    {
      "start": 241.43,
      "end": 241.51,
      "text": "Oh."
    },
    {
      "start": 241.89,
      "end": 247.67,
      "text": "근데 가족들이 역시 최고라는 생각을 하게 되는 연결이었어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 247.67,
      "end": 247.91,
      "text": "그렇죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 247.93,
      "end": 248.45,
      "text": "역시 가족."
    },
    {
      "start": 248.81,
      "end": 249.53,
      "text": "가족이 힘."
    },
    {
      "start": 249.65,
      "end": 249.85,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 250.61,
      "end": 252.09,
      "text": "자, 표현들 점검해 볼까요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 252.73,
      "end": 254.33,
      "text": "Sing it, acapella."
    },
    {
      "start": 254.71,
      "end": 256.59,
      "text": "Sing it, acapella."
    },
    {
      "start": 256.67,
      "end": 258.31,
      "text": "Acapella is one word, I think."
    },
    {
      "start": 258.33,
      "end": 258.57,
      "text": "그렇죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 258.79,
      "end": 259.35,
      "text": "Acapella."
    },
    {
      "start": 259.61,
      "end": 262.83,
      "text": "그런데 제가 궁금해가지고 사전도 찾아봤는데"
    },
    {
      "start": 262.83,
      "end": 265.75,
      "text": "진짜 A가 띄어져 있더라고요."
    },
    {
      "start": 266.47,
      "end": 267.59,
      "text": "아capella, 이렇게."
    },
    {
      "start": 267.85,
      "end": 268.43,
      "text": "아capella."
    },
    {
      "start": 268.79,
      "end": 270.89,
      "text": "Many times it's written as one word."
    },
    {
      "start": 270.93,
      "end": 271.41,
      "text": "그러니까요."
    },
    {
      "start": 271.47,
      "end": 274.61,
      "text": "마치 고유명사처럼 아capella 이렇게 붙어 있을 것 같은데"
    },
    {
      "start": 274.61,
      "end": 276.17,
      "text": "띄어져서 쓰이더라고요."
    },
    {
      "start": 276.17,
      "end": 279.39,
      "text": "Do you like to sing acapella or accompanied?"
    },
    {
      "start": 280.03,
      "end": 282.01,
      "text": "I've never done it before."
    },
    {
      "start": 282.47,
      "end": 283.73,
      "text": "Oh, you've done it here."
    },
    {
      "start": 284.07,
      "end": 285.27,
      "text": "When we talk and I say,"
    },
    {
      "start": 285.33,
      "end": 286.27,
      "text": "Hey, what's that song?"
    },
    {
      "start": 286.45,
      "end": 287.97,
      "text": "You sing a little bit acapella."
    },
    {
      "start": 288.09,
      "end": 288.57,
      "text": "그러네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 288.87,
      "end": 290.07,
      "text": "멀리 있지 않았네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 290.21,
      "end": 290.97,
      "text": "저도 했었네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 291.09,
      "end": 292.01,
      "text": "그것도 아capella예요."
    },
    {
      "start": 292.45,
      "end": 292.99,
      "text": "어, 그래요."
    },
    {
      "start": 293.13,
      "end": 293.63,
      "text": "무반주."
    },
    {
      "start": 293.77,
      "end": 295.05,
      "text": "무반주로 노래하다."
    },
    {
      "start": 295.31,
      "end": 296.83,
      "text": "아, 이렇게 와닿는 설명."
    },
    {
      "start": 296.99,
      "end": 297.39,
      "text": "감사합니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 298.61,
      "end": 300.07,
      "text": "Sorry for interrupting."
    },
    {
      "start": 300.33,
      "end": 301.99,
      "text": "Sorry for interrupting."
    },
    {
      "start": 302.37,
      "end": 303.87,
      "text": "방해해서 죄송합니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 303.87,
      "end": 305.55,
      "text": "라는 의미로 쓰입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 305.71,
      "end": 306.79,
      "text": "I'm so sorry for interrupting,"
    },
    {
      "start": 307.01,
      "end": 309.07,
      "text": "but I have something to say to you."
    },
    {
      "start": 309.17,
      "end": 309.39,
      "text": "그렇죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 309.39,
      "end": 312.81,
      "text": "뭔가 진짜 이야기하고 싶은 내용은 뒤에 따르기 마련이죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 313.31,
      "end": 314.95,
      "text": "Class of 89."
    },
    {
      "start": 315.23,
      "end": 316.53,
      "text": "A long time ago."
    },
    {
      "start": 316.67,
      "end": 316.81,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 317.57,
      "end": 320.45,
      "text": "89년도 졸업생이라는 표현이 되겠습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 320.65,
      "end": 322.51,
      "text": "한국에서 팔고 학번이라고 하지만."
    },
    {
      "start": 322.67,
      "end": 322.75,
      "text": "그렇죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 322.97,
      "end": 324.25,
      "text": "This is the 졸업년도."
    },
    {
      "start": 324.25,
      "end": 328.09,
      "text": "아, 89년도 졸업생이라는 의미로"
    },
    {
      "start": 328.09,
      "end": 329.47,
      "text": "Class of 89."
    },
    {
      "start": 330.11,
      "end": 331.59,
      "text": "과연 누구의 이야기일까요?"
